11 Service Oklahoma shall notify the license holder within three (3)
12 days of reinstatement that the license holder shall apply for a new
13 driver license pursuant to subsection A of Section 6-209 of this
14 title.
15 D. Service Oklahoma is hereby authorized to shall enter into
16 agreements with persons whose license to operate a motor vehicle or
17 commercial motor vehicle has been suspended or revoked, for issuance
18 of a provisional license subject to any restrictions imposed by law
19 or a court order. The provisional license would allow such persons
20 to drive from 6:00 a.m. to 11:59 p.m. Driving privileges for a
21 provisional license are limited from 12:00 a.m. to 5:59 a.m. to
22 driving:
23 1. Between their place of residence and their place of
24 employment or potential employment;
SB216 HFLR Page 5
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 2. During the scope and course of their employment;
2 3. Between their place of residence and a college, university
3 or technology center;
4 4. Between their place of residence and their child’s school or
5 day care provider;
6 5. Between their place of residence and a place of worship; or
7 6. Between their place of residence and any court-ordered
8 treatment program,
9 with the condition that such persons pay a minimum total of Five
10 Dollars ($5.00) per month toward the satisfaction of outstanding
11 fees, including, but not limited to, provisional license fees,
12 warrant fees, court costs or fees, driver license or commercial
13 driver license reinstatement fees. Service Oklahoma may suspend or
14 revoke a provisional license pursuant to this section if the person
15 fails to honor the payment plan. The person may re-enroll in the
16 provisional driver license program.
17 E. Any person convicted of an offense specified in paragraph 1,
18 4, or 8 of subsection A of Section 6-205 of this title shall not be
19 eligible for a provisional license.
20 F. Any violation of law by the person holding the provisional
21 license that would result in the suspension or revocation of a
22 driver license, except for the failure to pay fines, fees, or other
23 financial obligations if the person is participating in a payment
24 plan, shall result in the revocation of the provisional license.
